ng that for the latter, it is less the inductive character of geometry that makes it empirical, and rather the regulative requirement that the system of natural science be empirically closed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aGeometryxPhilosophy. 4aHelmholtz, Hermann von. 4aKant, Immanuel. 4aPhilosophie / Deutscher Idealismus. 4aPhilosophie / Kant. 4aPhilosophie / Wissenschaftstheorie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aWissenschaftstheorie. 4aphilosophy of science. 70(DE-601)1062002590(DE-588)4045791-6aPhilosophie2gnd 70(DE-601)1063188020(DE-588)4020236-7aGeometrie2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE UND GESCHICHTE 2009z9783110219500oZDB-23-DGE0 cprintz978311018391740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110217209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110217209.jpg  a978-3-11-021952-4  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009b2009  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  